  "prompt": "What are the symptoms of anxiety?",
  "response": "Anxiety can manifest in various ways, and its symptoms can differ from person to person. Common symptoms of anxiety include:\n\n1. **Emotional Symptoms:**\n   - Excessive worry or fear\n   - Feelings of apprehension or dread\n   - Irritability or restlessness\n   - Difficulty concentrating or focusing\n   - Feeling overwhelmed or out of control\n\n2. **Physical Symptoms:**\n   - Increased heart rate or palpitations\n   - Sweating\n   - Trembling or shaking\n   - Shortness of breath\n   - Muscle tension\n   - Fatigue\n   - Headaches\n   - Stomach issues (such as nausea or diarrhea)\n   - Sleep disturbances (insomnia or restless sleep)\n\n3. **Behavioral Symptoms:**\n   - Avoidance of certain situations or places\n   - Changes in appetite or eating habits\n   - Social withdrawal\n   - Decreased participation in activities once enjoyed\n\nSevere or chronic anxiety can lead to anxiety disorders, which may require professional treatment. If you or someone you know is experiencing significant anxiety symptoms, it's advisable to seek help from a mental health professional.",
